      "abstract": "Despite the scholarly consensus regarding the logical importance of Paul\u2019s reference to baptism in Gal. 3.27, there has been hardly any sustained analysis of why such a brief reference could be effective. With the recent emergence of interdisciplinary methods from cognitive science, memory studies, notions of embodiment, and ritual theories, this study explores the social impact of Paul\u2019s reference to baptism. Paul simultaneously reinforces his authority over, and solidarity with, the Galatian communities in a \u2018misrecognized\u2019 manner \u2013 neither of which could be claimed by the \u2018agitators\u2019 against whom he is arguing.",
